criteria.textblock:
        Inclusion Criteria:

          1. age ≥18 years;

          2. HF diagnosis regardless of cause as defined by the Framingham criteria and satisfying
             the European Society of Cardiology guidelines;

        Exclusion Criteria:

          1. metallic joint prostheses, cardiac stent or pacemakers, decompensated cirrhosis,
             pregnancy and limb amputations (due to bioimpedance technique limitations);

          2. no prior diagnosis of pulmonary fibrosis (due to lung ultrasonography limitations);

          3. absence of congenital heart disease
